{"word": "bubbling", "meanings": [{"pos": "v", "definition": "form, produce, or emit bubbles", "synonyms": ["bubble"], "examples": ["The soup was bubbling"]}, {"pos": "v", "definition": "flow in an irregular current with a bubbling noise", "synonyms": ["ripple", "babble", "guggle", "burble", "bubble", "gurgle"], "examples": ["babbling brooks"]}, {"pos": "v", "definition": "rise in bubbles or as if in bubbles", "synonyms": ["bubble"], "examples": ["bubble to the surface"]}, {"pos": "v", "definition": "cause to form bubbles", "synonyms": ["bubble"], "examples": ["bubble gas through a liquid"]}, {"pos": "v", "definition": "expel gas from the stomach", "synonyms": ["burp", "bubble", "belch", "eruct"], "examples": ["In China it is polite to burp at the table"]}, {"pos": "s", "definition": "emitting or filled with bubbles as from carbonation or fermentation", "synonyms": ["bubbly", "foaming", "foamy", "frothy", "effervescing", "spumy"], "examples": ["bubbling champagne", "foamy (or frothy) beer"]}, {"pos": "s", "definition": "marked by high spirits or excitement", "synonyms": ["effervescent", "frothy", "scintillating", "sparkly"], "examples": ["his fertile effervescent mind", "scintillating personality", "a row of sparkly cheerleaders"]}]}